IAST 2023 is a multi-fraternity AYUSH event, to be hosted at Nishagandhi Auditorium at Thiruvananthapuram, from 13 to 15 January 2023.

Key motive of the summit is to promote high quality research and academic discourse of AYUSH medical systems. Conduct seminars on cost effective AYUSH services, promotion of AYUSH systems, strengthening of health educational systems.  Quality control of Ayurveda, Siddha and Unani & Homoeopathy (ASU &H) drugs and sustainable availability of ASU & H raw-materials will be addressed in the summit.

Press Network of India (PNI) a registered media society having pan-India presence, along Santigiri Ashram, an organization diligently promoting AYUSH across the globe and leading organisations of AYUSH practitioners like QPHA (Qualified Private Homeopath’s Association) along with likeminded organizations are organizing the summit. IMC (International Malayali Council), a prominent social and cultural organization is making every effort to make the Summit a unique success

To publicize the Summit, awareness sessions coupled with medical camps are scheduled at  prominent locations: within Kerala and neighboring states .

Medical Camps
Specialized Clinics for critical illness like CANCER and HEART ailments .
The Summit has over 40 specialized clinics from all departments of AYUSH- Ayurveda, Yoga and Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homeopathy. The clinics are manned by specialists in critical illnesses like cancer, cardiac, kidney, and liver, pulmonary and also life-style related. There speciality clinics for senior citizens (geriatric ailments), women and children. There will be separate centers for traditional medicines and alternate therapy.


Highlights Of IAST 2023
3000+ Deligates and Celebrated Speakers
Over 3000 delegates from reputed health related Institutions from India and abroad. Speakers specialized in AYUSH system of medical science and therapy from India and abroad.

