Venue -Nishagandhi Auditorium and Jawahar Balabhavan, Thiruvananthapuram
Nishagandhi is a sprawling natural beauty that is in the heart of the Historical capital city of the god’s own country, Kerala. It is easy to locate, just five kilometers away from Thiruvananthapuram International Airport and less than three kilometers from Thiruvananthapuram Central Railway station and State Transport Bus Depot. The world famous Kovalam beach is just 15 km away and Kanyakumari is just two hours away. Nearby we have the lush green herbal mountains Agasthya mountains, known for rare medicinal herbs like the lifesaving mritasanjeevani and near to that mountain we have the misty hills of Ponmudy, a wonderful tourist destination. Just 40 kms north of Thiruvananthapuram, we have the ever enthralling natural beach Varkalala, known for its lofty cliffs. The world famous Sri Padmanabha Temple in Thiruvananthapuram is another pious destination for the delegates

Address: Nishagandhi Auditorium, Kanaka Nagar, Nanthancodu, Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala 695033


Thiruvananthapuram
Thiruvananthapuram also known as Trivandrum, is the capital and the largest city of the Indian state of Kerala.

Getting by a train
The nearest rail station from Nishagandhi Auditorium is Thampanoor, which is about 3.2 kilometres away with in the town. Once you reach at the station, you can hire a Taxi or Autorickshaw that will drive you to the Nishagandhi Auditorium.

National Rail
Additional Details
If you are arriving at Thiruvananthapuram airport   then you can go by Bus or hire a taxi or autorickshaw to Nishagandhi Auditorium  and it is about 6.7 kilometres away.

Thiruvananthapuram also known as Trivandrum, is the capital and the largest city of the Indian state of Kerala  is a major tourist centre, known for the Padmanabhaswamy Temple, the beaches of Kovalam and Varkala, the backwaters of Poovar and Anchuthengu and its Western Ghats tracts of Ponmudi and the Agastya Mala.

 

Our Location  Nishagandhi Auditorium Thiruvananthapuram is well-connected by road ,rail and airport. Airport is about 6.7 kilometers  Rail is about 3.2 kilometres away


